      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW VERA (6) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 8 lengths at Richmond in a handy 18.30 beating Shacoby Lad. Winner at her latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. In form and can go on with it. MARKET MAVERICK (1) has missed the frame the last couple but was a Grade 5 winner three back (20.95) at Nowra over 365m. Can turn it around this time. STEAL A MARCH (8) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Written In Gold (19.42) in a Grade 5. Chased the leaders and with a clean run can be prominent. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Expected to be in this for a long way. BEERS AND BANTER (2) is in the mix after placing last time out.",
